                        <h5>Why did I make Game DB?</h5>
                        <p>Game DB was created as a way to learn certain technologies involved in making websites and goes back to 2015. Originally it was to track players and rank them.
                            Then I started to track other bits of information that the <a href="/steam-api">Steam APIs</a> gave.
                            Then started to track as much as I could, all to display in a friendly manner for gamers.</p>

                        <h5>How can I contact you?</h5>
                        <p>Game DB is not affiliated with Steam, please contact them <a href="https://help.steampowered.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.
                            <br>Otherwise, use our <a href="/chat">chat</a> or <a href="/contact">contact</a> pages.</p>

                        <h5>Can I contribute to Game DB?</h5>
                        <p>
                            Yes! As Game DB gets more visitors, it's hardware constantly needs upgrading and workng on. Please consider <a href="/donate">donating</a> to help out.
                            <br/>Or help directly with the website on <a href="https://github.com/gamedb" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
                        </p>

                        <h5>Why are some pages a dark green theme?</h5>
                        <p>This is what the Steam client used to look like!</p>

                        <h5 id="trend-score">How is the app trend value calculated</h5>
                        <p>The algorithm is taken from <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/49604913/472084" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this post</a> and is likely to change.</p>

                        <h5>Why is a player missing?</h5>
                        <p>Game DB only knows about players that are added manually. If you are missing, you can add your profile or login to do it automatically.</p>

                        <h5>Why does a player have no rank?</h5>
                        <p>
                            Ranks get updated daily, so please check back tomorrow. If it has been longer, it may be because your privacy settings stop us from seeing your information.
                            You can allow access by updating your <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://steamcommunity.com/my/edit/settings">privacy settings</a>.
                        </p>

                        <h5>Why do some updates not show in the queues?</h5>
                        <p>If an update goes directly the the front of the queue, it will not show on the queue charts.</p>

                        <h5>How are Twitch streamers calculated</h5>
                        <p>Only the viewers from the top 100 streamers are included in the counts on Game DB.</p>

                        <h5>Where do we get the data from?</h5>
                        <p>Either from a <a href="/steam-api">Steam API</a> or by pretending to be a Steam client using <a href="https://github.com/SteamRE/SteamKit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SteamKit</a>.</p>

                        <h5 id="app-scores">How are app scores calculated?</h5>
                        <p>Using <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Additive_smoothing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Additive Smoothing</a></p>

                        <h5>Can I see the Game DB source code</h5>
                        <p>Game DB is fully open sourced on <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://github.com/gamedb">GitHub</a> to see exactly what's going on under the hood.</p>
